# Message Channel Domain

Authoritative contract: `docs/platforms/backend/contracts/message-channel-domain.md`.

## Separation

- `MessageChannel` stores **delivery credentials** only (SMTP / Ad Whats), not message subject/body/variable maps.
- Do **not** add `EJTMAA_EMAIL` to `messageChannelType`. Platform-mailer templates use **no** channel row (template FK null).

## Naming

- Channel type enum values: `CUSTOM_EMAIL` | `ADWHATS` | `ADWHATS_PRO`.
- Never spell Ad Whats as `AD_WHATS` / `AD_WHATS_PRO`.
- Discriminator field on the model is `type` (repo-native with `Meeting.type`).
- Do not confuse `_MessageChannelType` with `_MessageTemplateType` (template kinds include `EJTMAA_EMAIL`).

## Status and connectivity

- `messageChannelStatus`: `ACTIVE` | `DISABLED`, default **`ACTIVE`**.
- `MessageChannelModel.testConnection(): Promise<boolean>` is the connectivity hook (stub until SMTP/Ad Whats clients ship).
- Create/update call `testConnection()` after writing credentials: `true` → `ACTIVE`, `false` → `DISABLED`. Status is not client-owned.

## Write path

- Customer ability: `MESSAGE_CHANNEL` (`create` | `read` | `update` | `delete`) on `Customer` with org ownership.
- Requester `@requester("messageChannel")` — website map `customer.messageChannel`.
- Joi requires credential columns by `type`; unused branches `joi.any().optional().allow(null, "").strip()` then flat `?? null` writes (see `requester-type-conditional-strip.mdc`).
- List filter `_MessageChannelFilter`: optional `type` + `status`. Template channel picker always sends `status: ACTIVE`.
- Update **locks** `type` to the existing row.
- `read` values must **not** echo `messageChannel` id (same as member `read` / `member` id).
- `read` `type` uses `toEnumForSelect(..., "messageChannelType")` — see `docs/platforms/backend/patterns/requester-read-select-hydrate.md`.
- GQL SDL may expose credential columns including `smtp_password` / `adwhats_token` (product choice: no special secret omission).

## GQL / ORM wiring

- Customer roots: `messageChannels` / `messageChannel(id)` via `MessageChannelBridge` + `CustomerOrganizationOwnedBridgeBase`.
- `OrganizationBridge.GetOneParent` must include `MessageChannelModel` for `_MessageChannel.organization`.
- Local registry `backend/.types/models.ts` must include `"MessageChannel"`.
- After SDL changes: backend `yarn generate-types`, then mirror `base`/`customer` SDL + generated types into `website/` per `gql-schemas-bridges-general.mdc`.
